  .---.
 | ^_^ | Clyde: An AUR helper that creates a local repo 
 |     |   from which pacman install packages.
 |.-.-.|   

Initial testing release
 - Add packages to repo defined in /etc/clyde.conf with
     `clyde -S [name of package]`
 - Update pacman sync database after building packages with -y
 - Add package to repo from local taurball with 
     `clyde -U /path/to/taurball.tar.gz [pkgname]`
